{"can_edit": true, "from": {"id": "1646843124", "name": "Micha\u00ebl Caron Couturier"}, "revision": "10153924177475019", "updated_time": "2014-02-18T07:27:48+0000", "can_delete": true, "created_time": "2013-02-25T22:10:14+0000", "message": "<p><strong>Recommended distro to start :</strong></p><p><br /></p>Xubuntu 12.04.4 LTS<br /><p><br /></p><p><strong>32 bits or 64 bits :</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>Under 4Gb of ram 32 bits is better. At 4Gb or better, use 64 bits or a 32 bits PAE kernel that will allow to use the ram over 3,5Gb<br /></p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Easy suggestion to make it even more lightweight and fast :</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>sudo apt-get install openbox obconf</p><p>Then follow this tutorial :</p><p><a href=\"#\" role=\"button\"></a><a href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fopenbox.org%2Fwiki%2FHelp%3AXFCE%2FOpenbox&amp;h=xAQFXRFcG&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" onmouseover=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/openbox.org\\/wiki\\/Help:XFCE\\/Openbox&quot;);\" onclick=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/l.facebook.com\\/l.php?u=http\\u00253A\\u00252F\\u00252Fopenbox.org\\u00252Fwiki\\u00252FHelp\\u00253AXFCE\\u00252FOpenbox&amp;h=xAQFXRFcG&amp;s=1&quot;);\">http://openbox.org/wiki/Help:XFCE/Openbox</a></a><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><b>More into it :</b><br /><br /><a href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fubuntuguide.org%2Fwiki%2FUbuntu_Precise&amp;h=LAQHf9ECj&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" onmouseover=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/ubuntuguide.org\\/wiki\\/Ubuntu_Precise&quot;);\" onclick=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/l.facebook.com\\/l.php?u=http\\u00253A\\u00252F\\u00252Fubuntuguide.org\\u00252Fwiki\\u00252FUbuntu_Precise&amp;h=LAQHf9ECj&amp;s=1&quot;);\">http://ubuntuguide.org/wiki/Ubuntu_Precise</a></a><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Troubleshooting advice :</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>Use Google and seek for keywords related to your problem and the word Ubuntu. Ubuntu being the base distro of Mint, this will give out more results to help you.</p><p><br /></p><p>Use Google translate to seek for the amazing french documention of Ubuntu that may be fairly decent for beginners also.</p><p><br /></p><p><a href=\"#\" role=\"button\"></a><a href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.linuxquestions.org%2F&amp;h=VAQHheY2J&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" onmouseover=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/www.linuxquestions.org\\/&quot;);\" onclick=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/l.facebook.com\\/l.php?u=http\\u00253A\\u00252F\\u00252Fwww.linuxquestions.org\\u00252F&amp;h=VAQHheY2J&amp;s=1&quot;);\">http://www.linuxquestions.org/</a></a></p><p><a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.askubuntu.com%2F&amp;h=dAQEZJGRF&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" onmouseover=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/www.askubuntu.com\\/&quot;);\" onclick=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/l.facebook.com\\/l.php?u=http\\u00253A\\u00252F\\u00252Fwww.askubuntu.com\\u00252F&amp;h=dAQEZJGRF&amp;s=1&quot;);\">http://www.askubuntu.com</a></p><p><br /></p><p><a href=\"#\" role=\"button\"></a><a href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fdoc.ubuntu-fr.org%2F&amp;h=kAQHjrLqV&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" onmouseover=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/doc.ubuntu-fr.org\\/&quot;);\" onclick=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/l.facebook.com\\/l.php?u=http\\u00253A\\u00252F\\u00252Fdoc.ubuntu-fr.org\\u00252F&amp;h=kAQHjrLqV&amp;s=1&quot;);\">http://doc.ubuntu-fr.org/</a></a> (french)  or</p><p><strong>https://wiki</strong>.<strong>ubuntuusers</strong>.de/ (german)</p><p>&#123;source of advices about &quot;pure&quot; Ubuntu-distros <strong><a href=\"#\" role=\"button\"></a><a href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwiki.ubuntuusers.de%2FEinsteiger&amp;h=SAQHh_8Ln&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" onmouseover=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/wiki.ubuntuusers.de\\/Einsteiger&quot;);\" onclick=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/l.facebook.com\\/l.php?u=http\\u00253A\\u00252F\\u00252Fwiki.ubuntuusers.de\\u00252FEinsteiger&amp;h=SAQHh_8Ln&amp;s=1&quot;);\">http://wiki.ubuntuusers.de/Einsteiger</a></a> </strong>&#125;</p><p><br /></p><p><em><strong>*Xfce is the base of most of the LTS of Ubuntu and Linux Mint. It is stable, well featured and lightweight enough for any use*</strong></em></p><p><br /></p><p><em><strong>*LTS releases have 5 years of desktop and server support, including 2 years for new hardware  support, regular releases only get 9 months of support without added  hardware support for example it gained EFI, Secureboot and hybrid graphics support with updates*</strong></em></p>", "subject": "Recommendations for beginners", "id": "10152649184365019", "icon": "https://fbstatic-a.akamaihd.net/rsrc.php/v2/y7/r/8zhNI-VGpiI.png"}